<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hotly" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hotly,</orth> 1) contrary to coldly, with heat: <cit><quote>Titan did h. overlook them,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 178" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 178</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>an oven stopped burneth more h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 178" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 178</bibl></cit><lb />2) ardently, eagerly: <bibl n="shak. luc 716" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 716</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.4.68" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 4, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 4.5.117" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 5, 117</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.166" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 166</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.2.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 2, 44</bibl>.
